---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Fisher & Paykel Stove Repair | Southern California | 90cm Pro-Style + Dual-Fuel";
const description = "Fisher & Paykel stove repair across Southern California — 90 Series 90cm freestanding, Pro-Style + dual-fuel, 2-oven variants. NZ premium + Huntington Beach LA-local parts. $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/fisher-paykel-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Fisher & Paykel still a New Zealand brand after Haier acquisition?",
    a: "Fisher & Paykel (F&P) was founded in Auckland, New Zealand in 1934 and was acquired by Haier Group in 2012 (full 100% ownership). F&P retains significant NZ engineering presence, product identity, and brand heritage — Haier has kept F&P operating as a distinct premium brand rather than folding it into Haier mainstream product lines. For North American distribution, F&P operates a parts warehouse in <b>Huntington Beach, California</b> — the biggest practical service advantage for LA households: 1-3 day parts delivery to LA authorized service on common F&P components, similar LA-local advantage to Hestan (Anaheim factory) and Thermador (BSH Irvine). F&P sibling brand DCS (Dynamic Cooking Systems) specializes in outdoor-kitchen grills and also routes through Huntington Beach distribution."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the 90cm format about — and which F&P stove lines are common in LA?",
    a: "F&P's signature is the <b>90cm (approximately 36\") European-format freestanding pro-style stove</b>. 90cm maps closely to US 36\" (the volume luxury-kitchen size), so F&P fits US luxury-kitchen installs naturally. <b>F&P Pro 90 Series</b> is the flagship — 90cm freestanding pro-style with 5-burner configurations, dual-fuel (gas cooktop + electric convection oven) + all-gas variants, stainless build quality. <b>2-oven + 3-oven variants</b> extend the lineup for larger-format installs. <b>60cm units</b> fit compact kitchens similar to Smeg territory, though less common than 90cm in LA volume. LA F&P installs concentrate where NZ premium + Huntington Beach parts-proximity is specifically valued — OC custom kitchens (closest to Huntington Beach warehouse), Pacific Palisades + Brentwood architectural luxury, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal custom, Pasadena established luxury."
  },
  {
    q: "Does the Huntington Beach warehouse really matter for LA F&P service?",
    a: "Yes — it's the defining practical advantage of owning F&P in LA. F&P's Huntington Beach parts warehouse is one of three LA-local parts-proximate luxury brands (alongside Hestan Anaheim and Thermador-Bosch-Gaggenau BSH Irvine). Typical parts delivery to authorized LA service on common F&P components: 1-3 days. Compare: Wolf ships 5-7 days from Madison WI, Viking 4-6 days from Greenwood MS, BlueStar 5-10 days from Blandon PA, Fulgor 5-10 days through US distribution. Huntington Beach proximity means F&P can typically be returned to service within 48-72 hours on straightforward repairs vs 7-10+ days on out-of-state luxury brands. For households hosting events or with cooking-critical routines, that parts-window difference materially affects household experience."
  },
  {
    q: "F&P Pro-Style 90 Series burner not lighting — diagnostic?",
    a: "Standard pro-range diagnostic with F&P-specific considerations: (1) orifice verification on LP / NG / 90cm-format mismatch; orifice $180–$280 per burner; (2) spark-module ignition $260–$400 at 8-12 year mark (F&P-specific spec); (3) ignitor tip clean / replace $200–$300; (4) flame-failure thermocouple $220–$320 (EU safety standard); (5) burner cap seating + port clean $160–$240 per burner; (6) gas valve $300–$440; (7) regulator $220–$340. F&P CookSurface Sensor-Controlled gas models (flame-monitoring tech) have additional diagnostic path — sensor module $280–$420 when flame-monitoring logic is the fault source. Huntington Beach parts channel supports 1-3 day LA-local lead on common F&P components."
  },
  {
    q: "F&P oven temperature drift on 90 Series — what's failing?",
    a: "Standard dual-fuel diagnostic: (1) temperature sensor drift at 5-8 years; sensor $220–$320; (2) bake element (electric oven-side) $320–$460; (3) convection fan motor $340–$500; (4) convection element $320–$460; (5) control board $460–$660; (6) thermal fuse / high-limit $240–$340; (7) oven door rope seal $180–$280. F&P 90cm oven cavity is similar to US 36\" format, so convection distribution diagnostic follows conventional pro-range patterns. Sensor calibration on F&P is typically straightforward; Huntington Beach parts supports 1-3 day lead if sensor replacement needed."
  },
  {
    q: "F&P vs Viking vs Wolf in LA — how to choose?",
    a: "<b>F&P (this page)</b> — Haier 2012+ NZ heritage, 90cm pro-style freestanding, Huntington Beach LA-local parts 1-3 day. Positioned as NZ-premium with LA-local parts-proximity advantage. <b>Viking</b> — Middleby Greenwood MS, 23k ProFlow BTU dual-stacked, Brilliance 20+ color program, 4-6 day parts. See <a href='/brands/viking-stove-repair/'>Viking stove repair</a>. <b>Wolf</b> — Sub-Zero Group Madison WI, 20k dual-stacked, coordinated Sub-Zero/Wolf/Cove suite, 5-7 day parts. See <a href='/brands/wolf-stove-repair/'>Wolf stove repair</a>. Choice drivers: F&P for LA-local parts-proximity + NZ-premium engineering + 90cm Euro-format matching US 36\"; Viking for heritage pro-grade + color program + Middleby scale; Wolf for Sub-Zero suite integration + heritage residential luxury."
  },
  {
    q: "DCS is sibling to F&P — is DCS service the same channel?",
    a: "<b>DCS (Dynamic Cooking Systems)</b> is F&P's sibling brand focused on outdoor-kitchen grills, cooktops, and specialty outdoor appliances. DCS shares the Huntington Beach parts warehouse and US distribution network with F&P. Both brands route through the same LA-local parts advantage. DCS service is typically outdoor-grill focused (freestanding grills, built-in grill heads, outdoor burners) rather than residential indoor stove; residential indoor stove service is the F&P side of the portfolio. For households with both F&P indoor + DCS outdoor, our service handles both through the unified parts channel. This page covers F&P indoor residential stove only — outdoor grill service is a different product scope."
  },
  {
    q: "What does F&P stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical F&P bands: orifice swap (per burner) $180–$280; burner cap $140–$220; spark-module $260–$400; ignitor tip $200–$300; flame-failure thermocouple $220–$320; air-mix adjustment $180–$260; gas-line regulator $220–$340; gas valve $300–$440; oven igniter $260–$380; bake element $320–$460; convection element $320–$460; convection fan motor $340–$500; temperature sensor $220–$320; thermal fuse $240–$340; oven door rope seal $180–$280; control board $460–$660; CookSurface Sensor module $280–$420 (if equipped); 90cm-format specific trim or panel parts $180–$340 depending on item. F&P service runs comparable to Viking / Wolf on individual parts with meaningfully faster service-window through Huntington Beach 1-3 day parts-proximity advantage."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Fisher & Paykel Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": "+1-424-325-0520", "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Fisher & Paykel Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Fisher & Paykel stove repair across LA — 90 Series 90cm freestanding pro-style, 2-oven + 3-oven variants, dual-fuel + all-gas, 60cm compact variants. NZ heritage since 1934, Haier 2012+. Huntington Beach CA parts warehouse LA-local 1-3 day parts advantage. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Fisher & Paykel", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/fisher-paykel/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Fisher & Paykel Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>F&P stove service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Fisher & Paykel › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Fisher & Paykel Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Fisher & Paykel is the New Zealand appliance brand founded in Auckland in 1934, now owned by Haier Group since the 2012 full acquisition. F&P has retained NZ engineering presence, distinct product identity, and premium positioning under Haier — and for LA service the defining practical advantage is F&P's <b>Huntington Beach, California</b> parts warehouse, which delivers 1-3 day parts to LA authorized service on common components (similar LA-local advantage to Hestan Anaheim and Thermador-Bosch-Gaggenau BSH Irvine). F&P 90 Series 90cm (~36") freestanding pro-style ranges anchor the LA residential stove lineup with 2-oven + 3-oven variants and dual-fuel + all-gas configurations. 60cm (~24") compact variants fit smaller-kitchen installs. Sibling DCS brand handles outdoor-kitchen grill service through the same Huntington Beach channel. Our LA F&P service concentrates in OC custom kitchens closest to Huntington Beach, Pacific Palisades + Brentwood architectural luxury, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal, Pasadena established luxury. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>NZ-founded 1934, Haier 2012+</b> — distinct premium identity retained</li>
      <li><b>Huntington Beach CA parts warehouse</b> — LA-local 1-3 day parts</li>
      <li><b>90cm Pro 90 Series + 60cm variants</b> — Euro-format spanning US 36" + 24"</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>F&P in LA — NZ premium with LA-local parts proximity</h2>
    <p>Fisher & Paykel occupies a specific LA luxury-stove position: NZ-heritage premium engineering + Haier 2012+ corporate scale + Huntington Beach LA-local parts-proximity. The Huntington Beach warehouse is the defining service advantage — most LA luxury-stove households don't think about parts-channel geography until they need a part, and then the difference between 1-3 days (F&P / Hestan / Thermador) vs 5-10 days (Viking / Wolf / BlueStar / Fulgor) is the difference between a weekend repair and a week-long downtime.</p>
    <p>Our LA F&P service geography concentrates where LA-local parts are most visible. OC custom kitchens — Newport Coast, Corona del Mar, Laguna Beach, Newport Beach, Irvine — sit closest to Huntington Beach with often 24-48 hour parts arrival. LA-side concentration: Pacific Palisades + Brentwood architectural luxury custom; Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury; Pasadena + San Marino established luxury; Bel Air + Beverly Hills luxury remodels. Service approach on 90 Series follows conventional pro-range diagnostic with F&P-specific parts through Huntington Beach channel — we carry common F&P igniters, thermocouples, sensors in LA dispatch. CookSurface Sensor-Controlled gas variants add a flame-monitoring diagnostic layer we handle during service.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>F&P stove failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>90 Series burner no-light</h3><p>Standard pro-range diagnostic. Orifice $180–$280 per burner; spark module $260–$400; thermocouple $220–$320.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>CookSurface Sensor module fault</h3><p>Flame-monitoring logic. Sensor module $280–$420 on equipped models.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven temperature drift</h3><p>Sensor $220–$320; control board $460–$660; thermal fuse $240–$340.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor</h3><p>Motor swap $340–$500. Convection element $320–$460.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven igniter glow-but-no-heat</h3><p>Igniter $260–$380 on F&P pro-range.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven door rope seal</h3><p>10+ year degradation. Seal $180–$280 per door.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>F&P stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro 90 Series (flagship)</h3><p>90cm (~36") freestanding pro-style. 5-burner. Dual-fuel + all-gas. Volume line in LA installs.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>2-Oven + 3-Oven variants</h3><p>Multi-oven configurations. Larger-format custom kitchens. Bel Air / Beverly Hills + coastal luxury.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>60cm Euro-format</h3><p>~24" width for compact luxury kitchens. Similar format to Smeg; less common than 90cm in LA.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>CookSurface Sensor gas</h3><p>Flame-monitoring technology. Dedicated sensor module. F&P-specific innovation.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>DCS sibling brand</h3><p>Outdoor-kitchen grills + specialty outdoor. Same Huntington Beach parts channel. Different product scope.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Huntington Beach parts warehouse</h3><p>LA-local 1-3 day parts delivery. Matches Hestan + Thermador for parts-proximity speed.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>F&P vs Hestan vs Thermador — three LA-local parts-proximate brands</h2>
    <p>Three luxury residential stove brands with LA-local parts warehouses. Rare category.</p>
    <p><b>F&P (this page)</b> — Huntington Beach warehouse, NZ-heritage premium, 90cm pro-style + multi-oven variants, Haier 2012+.</p>
    <p><b>Hestan</b> — Anaheim factory 70k sqft, Meyer Corp since 2014, Hestan Cue smart integration, Bordeaux + Matte color program. See <a href="/brands/hestan-stove-repair/">Hestan stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Thermador</b> — BSH Irvine warehouse, Pro Grand 36/48/60 + Pro Grand Steam, Star Burner + ExtraLow signature. See <a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>All three offer 1-3 day LA-local parts, a meaningful advantage over Viking / Wolf / BlueStar (4-10 day out-of-state). Choice drivers: F&P for NZ-heritage premium + 90cm Euro-format; Hestan for Cue smart + Bordeaux / Matte program; Thermador for BSH heritage + Pro Grand Steam + broadest installed base.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What F&P stove repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Orifice swap (per burner)</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>LP / NG mismatch</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Burner cap replacement</td><td>$140 – $220</td><td>Per burner</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spark-module ignition</td><td>$260 – $400</td><td>F&P-specific spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ignitor tip clean / replace</td><td>$200 – $300</td><td>Carbon / electrode wear</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Flame-failure thermocouple</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>EU safety standard</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CookSurface Sensor module</td><td>$280 – $420</td><td>Flame-monitoring tech</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas-line regulator</td><td>$220 – $340</td><td>Pressure stability</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve swap</td><td>$300 – $440</td><td>Stuck / restricted</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven igniter</td><td>$260 – $380</td><td>Pro-range oven-side</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bake element (dual-fuel)</td><td>$320 – $460</td><td>Electric oven-side</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Convection element</td><td>$320 – $460</td><td>Rear of cavity</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Convection fan motor</td><td>$340 – $500</td><td>Dual-fuel dependency</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature sensor</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>Oven accuracy</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermal fuse / high-limit</td><td>$240 – $340</td><td>Safety cutout</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven door rope seal</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Per door</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Control board</td><td>$460 – $660</td><td>Digital control</td></tr>
      <tr><td>90cm-format trim / panel parts</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Format-specific components</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/fisher-paykel/">Fisher & Paykel brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/hestan-stove-repair/">Hestan stove repair (LA-local Anaheim)</a> · <a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair (LA-local Irvine)</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA service areas — where our F&P stove calls come from</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>OC custom (closest to Huntington Beach)</h4><p>Huntington Beach · Newport Beach · Newport Coast · Corona del Mar · <a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a></p></div>
      <div><h4>Pacific Palisades + Brentwood</h4><p>Pacific Palisades · Brentwood · Rustic Canyon</p></div>
      <div><h4>Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes</h4><p>Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes · Redondo Beach</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pasadena + San Marino</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · La Cañada</p></div>
      <div><h4>Bel Air + Beverly Hills</h4><p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · Holmby Hills</p></div>
      <div><h4>Coastal luxury</h4><p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · Laguna Beach</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related F&P and LA-local parts-proximate pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/fisher-paykel/">Fisher & Paykel brand hub →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/hestan-stove-repair/">Hestan stove repair (LA-local Anaheim) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair (LA-local Irvine) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/wolf-stove-repair/">Wolf stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/stove-repair/">Stove repair (service hub) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/price-list/stove-repair-cost/">Stove repair cost guide →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>F&P stove repair — frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>F&P stove service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .model-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .model-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .section.alt .model-card { background: #fff; }
  .fail-block { background: #fff; border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
